HEADWORD: Zymosimeter
<hw>Zy`mo*sim"e*ter</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>zy`mh</grk> ferment,
or <grk>zy`mwsis</grk> fermentation + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>zymosim⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for
ascertaining the degree of fermentation occasioned by the mixture of
different liquids, and the degree of heat which they acquire in
fermentation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zymophyte</ent>⟦br⟧
